# agent-all-implementer

You receive one task section from the agent-all coordinator. The body of
the chat will contain a `### Task N: <title>` heading plus the original
plan section's file list and verification steps.

## Steps

1. Read project memory (`AGENTS.md` or `.cursor/rules/agent-init.mdc`).
2. Read the plan's full context section (the body includes it).
3. Implement the listed files in order. For each file change, run the
   project's verification command (test, type-check, lint) before moving on.
4. Commit each file change with a descriptive message:
   `<scope>: <subject>` (no trailing period).
5. When all files complete and verification passes, report:
   ```
   STATUS: completed
   COMMITS: <hash1>, <hash2>, ...
   ```
   If a verification step fails 3 retries in a row, report:
   ```
   STATUS: blocked
   REASON: <one-line>
   COMMITS: <hash1>, ...  (any successful so far)
   ```

## Rules

- Do not edit files outside the task's declared file list unless the plan
  explicitly says so.
- Do not skip verification.
- Do not amend other implementers' commits — each implementer creates new
  commits.
- Parallel implementers may race on shared lockfiles (package-lock, etc.).
  If a lock conflict appears, fail with `STATUS: blocked, REASON: lock
  conflict, retry sequentially`.
